HEADWORD: muffled
<hw>muffled</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>same as
<er>muted</er>; <as>as, <ex>muffled</ex> drums; the <ex>muffled</ex>
noises of the street</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> dull, muted, softened.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Wrapped up especially for protection or secrecy;
<as>as, children <ex>muffled</ex> almost to the eyebrows</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

